    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Hi @Lovely-Fellow \r\nIn your example showMore function is not called when you reach the bottom of the DataTable  because the sentinel is outside the scrolling area of that data table. \r\nThe DOM element of your sentinel need to be invisible in the viewport then revealed as we scroll down the DataTable.\r\n\r\nIt's not clear to me whether DataTable can support a sentinel inside the scrolling area, but there seem to be something that allow for server-side loading of data.  https://datatables.net/extensions/scroller/examples/initialisation/server-side_processing.html\r\nIf you can manage to get DataTable to call `lastRenderArgs.showMore()`, it should work as expected.",
